To find the $\goldE{\text{total}}$ height to the window, we start with the $\blueE{\text{length of the rope}}$, and add how many $\maroonD{\text{meters shorter}}$ the rope is. 

![](web+graphie://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-graphie/4a007e41290775aaaed5c76e2bef9ea45bd86a78)

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{Length of the rope}} + \maroonD{12}  &= \goldE{\text{Height of the window}} \\\\
\blueE{19} + \maroonD{12} &= \goldE{\Box}
\end{align}$
